featured_reviews.review_id:
Old and ancient mosques have something about them that attracts every history lover. Kali Masjid is another mosque in this list, located in Jalna, Maharashtra. Built by Jamshed Khan, holy saint, more than 400 years ago this mosque was built of black stone, making it a rare one. Also known as Jumma Masjid, it was built in AD 1557 and is rectangular in shape.

The Kali Masjid closed on three sides and there's an arcade in the front. There is also a verandah that has a sloping with three arches as support. The corners have been beautified with small fluted domes and the masjid contains extensive perforated stone work that you would fall in love with
